---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import ArticleSchema from '../../components/ArticleSchema.astro';
import TldrBox from '../../components/TldrBox.astro';
import FaqSection from '../../components/FaqSection.astro';
import ToolReview from '../../components/ToolReview.astro';
import { siteFromHost } from '../../content';
import { appBySlug } from '../../data/apps';

const site = siteFromHost();
const path = '/guides/selection-framework';
const title = 'How to Choose a Shopify Email Marketing Tool (2026)';
const desc = 'A practical Shopify email tool selection framework: compare 14 apps by lifecycle job, Shopify data, ownership, pricing model, consent, and a bounded pilot before you migrate.';
const slugs = ['sequenzy','klaviyo','omnisend','shopify-email','privy','drip','postscript','attentive','mailchimp','brevo','activecampaign','yotpo-email-sms','rejoiner','tinyemail'];
const apps = slugs.map((slug) => appBySlug(slug)!).filter(Boolean);
const faqs = [
  { question: 'How many Shopify email tools should make the shortlist?', answer: 'Keep three finalists: one primary lifecycle platform, one simpler fallback, and an optional SMS or capture specialist. A long list is useful for research; it is a poor pilot plan.' },
  { question: 'Should Shopify Email be the first tool I test?', answer: 'Test it when your requirement is campaigns, product announcements, and a small number of simple segments. Test a dedicated platform when cart recovery, replenishment, consent handoffs, or multi-step suppression are already revenue-critical.' },
  { question: 'How should I compare pricing?', answer: 'Use the last 90 days of sends, active profiles, peak-month volume, SMS usage, and implementation hours. Public starting prices are not quotes, and plans change; verify the vendor pricing page before approval.' },
  { question: 'What is the safest migration sequence?', answer: 'Inventory triggers and consent first, connect Shopify, rebuild one high-value flow, test suppression and attribution, then run a limited overlap. Do not switch every flow during a seasonal peak.' },
];
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={desc} site={site} path={path}>
  <ArticleSchema title={title} description={desc} siteName={site.name} domain={site.domain} path={path} />
  <section class="py-14 md:py-20">
    <div class="container">
      <a href="/guides" class="text-sm font-bold text-cyan-800">← All operator guides</a>
      <p class="editorial-kicker mt-6">Buying guide · Shopify email operations</p>
      <h1 class="hero-title mt-5 max-w-5xl">How to choose a Shopify email marketing tool</h1>
      <p class="mt-7 max-w-3xl text-xl leading-9 text-slate-700">Every app page says it supports Shopify, automation, and segmentation. The useful question is narrower: can this team run its three most valuable customer journeys, with the right catalog data, suppression rules, owner, and cost model? This framework turns that question into a scored shortlist.</p>
      <p class="mt-5 max-w-3xl text-lg leading-8 text-slate-600">The 14 options below cover native campaigns, lifecycle automation, capture, SMS, reviews and loyalty, CRM-led workflows, and developer-owned delivery. Treat the descriptions as fit guidance, not product guarantees: confirm current capabilities, plan limits, data retention, and Shopify app terms with each vendor.</p>
      <div class="mt-9 flex flex-wrap gap-3"><a class="btn btn-primary" href="/apps">Browse app profiles</a><a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/guides/pricing-models">Compare pricing models</a><a class="btn btn-secondary" href="/guides/implementation-plan">Plan implementation</a></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container pb-12">
    <TldrBox title="The shortlist in one minute" picks={[
      { label: 'Lifecycle-first', tool: 'Sequenzy', reason: 'Useful when a lean team needs guided sequence work and wants to model cost by sends.' },
      { label: 'Deepest commerce data', tool: 'Klaviyo', reason: 'A strong candidate when catalog, event, and predictive segmentation depth justify the operating model.' },
      { label: 'Fast multichannel start', tool: 'Omnisend', reason: 'Worth testing when standard email, SMS, and push journeys need to launch quickly.' },
      { label: 'Native campaign baseline', tool: 'Shopify Email', reason: 'A sensible control when the requirement is simple campaigns inside Shopify admin.' },
      { label: 'SMS specialist', tool: 'Postscript', reason: 'Evaluate as a channel layer when SMS consent, replies, and cart recovery matter.' },
    ]} />
    <div class="prose-shopify mt-12 max-w-4xl">
      <h2>Start with the job, not the vendor logo</h2>
      <p>Write the trigger, audience, suppression, product context, offer, and success metric for welcome, cart, post-purchase, replenishment, or winback. A platform that cannot express the highest-value job without a spreadsheet or custom webhook should not win because its demo looked polished.</p>
      <p>Then score the shortlist on six dimensions: lifecycle fit, Shopify data depth, total cost at projected volume, implementation capacity, channel ownership, and migration risk. A low score on a must-have workflow is a veto, not something to average away.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card mt-10 overflow-x-auto"><h2 class="px-5 py-4 font-serif text-2xl font-black">Six-dimension scorecard</h2><table class="data-table"><thead><tr><th>Dimension</th><th>Evidence to request</th><th>Veto condition</th></tr></thead><tbody>
      <tr><td>Lifecycle fit</td><td>Real trigger, delay, branch, suppression test</td><td>Core journey needs manual exports</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Shopify data</td><td>Order, product, customer, consent and event mapping</td><td>Required property is unavailable or delayed</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Total cost</td><td>12-month sends, profiles, SMS, seats and labor</td><td>Peak bill cannot be explained</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Ownership</td><td>Named person can edit and QA flows</td><td>Only an agency can maintain logic</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Channels</td><td>Email/SMS boundaries and suppression ownership</td><td>Two tools can message the same customer</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Migration</td><td>Consent export, DNS, history, overlap plan</td><td>Cutover is inside a peak trading window</td></tr>
    </tbody></table></div>
    <div class="card mt-10 overflow-x-auto"><h2 class="px-5 py-4 font-serif text-2xl font-black">Match the tool to the operating constraint</h2><table class="data-table"><thead><tr><th>Constraint</th><th>Start with</th><th>Watch closely</th></tr></thead><tbody>
      <tr><td>Simple campaigns and low setup capacity</td><td>Shopify Email, tinyEmail</td><td>Automation depth and reporting</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Deep behavioral commerce segmentation</td><td>Klaviyo, Drip</td><td>Profile pricing and owner time</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Fast email plus SMS rollout</td><td>Omnisend, Yotpo Email &amp; SMS</td><td>Message credits and collision rules</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Capture before lifecycle</td><td>Privy, Justuno</td><td>Consent source and downstream sync</td></tr>
      <tr><td>CRM or sales handoff</td><td>ActiveCampaign, Brevo</td><td>Shopify event and catalog detail</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Developer-owned transactional delivery</td><td>Resend, Postmark</td><td>Marketing consent and campaign tooling</td></tr>
    </tbody></table></div>
    <div class="card mt-10 overflow-x-auto"><h2 class="px-5 py-4 font-serif text-2xl font-black">Evidence to collect before signing</h2><table class="data-table"><thead><tr><th>Area</th><th>Ask for</th><th>Record</th></tr></thead><tbody>
      <tr><td>Pricing</td><td>Current plan calculator and peak-volume quote</td><td>Assumptions, overages, annual terms</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Data</td><td>Shopify sync fields, frequency, deletion behavior</td><td>Field map and test customer IDs</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Deliverability</td><td>Domain setup, suppression, complaint handling</td><td>DNS owner and escalation path</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Compliance</td><td>Consent export, SMS rules, regional controls</td><td>Source, timestamp, purpose, opt-out path</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Support</td><td>Response model and migration responsibility</td><td>Named contacts and scope boundaries</td></tr>
    </tbody></table></div>
  </section>

  <section class="container space-y-10 pb-16"><p class="editorial-kicker">14 tools, 14 different reasons to shortlist</p><h2 class="font-serif text-4xl font-black">Tool-by-tool fit and trade-offs</h2>
    {apps.map((app, i) => <ToolReview app={app} rank={i + 1} badge={i === 0 ? 'Start here if lifecycle is the constraint' : undefined} paragraphs={[
      `${app.name} is most relevant when the selection brief says “${app.bestFor.toLowerCase()}.” In a pilot, test one real Shopify journey rather than a template: use the store’s products, customer states, consent source, and suppression rules. Its ${app.category.toLowerCase()} positioning makes it a different candidate from a general-purpose email sender.`,
      `The trade-off is operational. ${app.name} should be scored on ${app.shopifyDepth.toLowerCase()} Shopify data and ${app.automationDepth.toLowerCase()} automation against the exact fields the store needs, not against a feature checklist. ${app.priceDetail}; treat “${app.pricing}” as a starting point and confirm current limits, SMS or usage charges, seats, onboarding, and overages on the official site before approval.`,
    ]} />)}
  </section>

  <section class="container pb-16"><div class="ledger-card"><p class="editorial-kicker">A bounded implementation pilot</p><h2 class="mt-3 font-serif text-3xl font-black">Seven days to test the decision</h2><ol class="mt-6 space-y-3 text-[17px] leading-8 text-slate-700"><li><strong>Day 1:</strong> export consent, document one journey, and freeze the control audience.</li><li><strong>Days 2–3:</strong> connect Shopify, map products and events, and send to internal test addresses.</li><li><strong>Days 4–5:</strong> run a small live cohort with purchase suppression, UTM tracking, and no overlapping incumbent flow.</li><li><strong>Days 6–7:</strong> compare delivered events, revenue quality, complaints, unsubscribes, margin, and operator hours.</li></ol><p class="mt-6 text-[17px] leading-8 text-slate-700">Keep the winner only if it passes the workflow, data, ownership, and cost gates. Use the <a class="link" href="/guides/consent-compliance">consent guide</a>, <a class="link" href="/guides/deliverability">deliverability playbook</a>, and <a class="link" href="/guides/flow-collision-prevention">collision checklist</a> during QA. For current product details, check each vendor’s official pricing and documentation links from the <a class="link" href="/apps">app directory</a>.</p></div></section>
  <FaqSection faqs={faqs} title="Shopify email tool selection FAQ" />
</BaseLayout>
